    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-01T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-01T15:00:00-05:00" n="234"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d234">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/10953a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PTN1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-01T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 1, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1597. Department’s 1476<note n="2" xml:id="d234fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_260">p. 260</ref>.</note> and
                    your 1764.<note n="3" xml:id="d234fn3">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_264">p. 264</ref>.</note>
                    British and French Governments are proposing to Allied Naval Council a unity of
                    command in the Mediterranean, just as there is now a unity of military command
                    on the western front. The Government of the United States is in entire agreement
                    with this view and instructions have been sent to <persName corresp="#p_SAWS1"
                        >Admiral Sims</persName> to give his support to the proposal to agree upon a
                    single naval commander for the forces in the Mediterranean. <pb facs="0388"
                        n="296" xml:id="pg_296"/> Please inform Italian Government of the views held
                    by the Government of the United States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
